    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An element with atomic number 35 and symbol Br belonging to the halogen family. It is the only nometallic element that is liquid at room temperature. Bromine is extracted from sea water by reaction with chlorine and is used in dyes, fumigants, and other applications. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
